# Cursor Rules

## Approach
You are performing spec-driven development. docs/SPEC.md is the source of truth for everything you build.

- Always align your output with SPEC.md
- If a request contradicts or is not covered by SPEC.md, stop and flag it before proceeding
- Never assume or invent requirements not in SPEC.md

## Tech stack
- Backend: FastAPI (Python)
- Frontend: Vue 3
- Database: SQLite
- ORM: SQLAlchemy

## Code style
- Keep code simple and readable over clever
- Add a short comment when a choice is non-obvious

## Database migrations
- Always use Alembic for database schema changes
- Every time a model is added or modified, generate an Alembic migration script before applying it
- Never modify the DB schema directly - always go through migrations
- Migration scripts must be reviewed before running
- Before starting any task, check `docs/user-stories/` for stories marked `In progress`. If one exists, continue it before starting anything new.
- When a story is complete, mark it as `Done`, commit all changes to the main branch with the message format: `feat: US-XXX - [US title]`, then suggest the next `To do` story.
- When writing user stories, always use `docs/templates/us-template.md` as the template.

## Testing
- Always generate pytest tests for backend endpoints alongside the code you write
- Always generate Vitest component tests for Vue components alongside the code you write
- Tests live next to the code they cover